{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775842408388,"sessionID":"ses_2878b748bffeFD7aGG0gqLqIfP","part":{"id":"prt_d7874b38a001V7tyovxA7PrZ5D","messageID":"msg_d7874a6de0017nW8505aRtyWkB","sessionID":"ses_2878b748bffeFD7aGG0gqLqIfP","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_a0a4adbdf2544febaf18fb41","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-004/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-004/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/workloadmanager  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (Design completed)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: Directory Scaffold\n11: \n12: - [ ] **1.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/` directory structure\n13: - [ ] **1.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` - API request/response DTOs\n14: - [ ] **1.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/service.go` - WorkloadManager interface definition\n15: - [ ] **1.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/client.go` - Kubernetes client initialization\n16: - [ ] **1.5** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` - Gin server setup and configuration\n17: - [ ] **1.6** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/` directory\n18: - [ ] **1.7** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/` directory\n19: - [ ] **1.8** Create `cmd/workload-manager/` directory for CLI entry point\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## Phase 2: API Types & Data Structures\n24: \n25: - [ ] **2.1** Define `APIResponse` struct in `types.go` - standard API response wrapper\n26: - [ ] **2.2** Define `APIError` struct in `types.go` - standard error response format (Kubernetes Status format)\n27: - [ ] **2.3** Define `PaginationRequest` struct in `types.go` - pagination parameters\n28: - [ ] **2.4** Define `PaginationResponse` struct in `types.go` - pagination metadata\n29: - [ ] **2.5** Define `AgentRuntimeListResponse` struct in `types.go`\n30: - [ ] **2.6** Define `CodeInterpreterListResponse` struct in `types.go`\n31: - [ ] **2.7** Define `CreateAgentRuntimeRequest` struct in `types.go`\n32: - [ ] **2.8** Define `CreateCodeInterpreterRequest` struct in `types.go`\n33: - [ ] **2.9** Define `UpdateAgentRuntimeRequest` struct in `types.go`\n34: - [ ] **2.10** Define `UpdateCodeInterpreterRequest` struct in `types.go`\n35: - [ ] **2.11** Define `Config` struct in `server.go` - server configuration with port, graceful shutdown timeout\n36: - [ ] **2.12** Define `Server` struct in `server.go` - HTTP server wrapper\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: ## Phase 3: Service Interface Implementation\n41: \n42: - [ ] **3.1** Define `WorkloadManager` interface in `service.go`\n43: - [ ] **3.2** Implement `workloadManagerImpl` struct in `service.go`\n44: - [ ] **3.3** Implement `NewWorkloadManager` constructor function\n45: - [ ] **3.4** Implement `CreateAgentRuntime` method\n46: - [ ] **3.5** Implement `GetAgentRuntime` method\n47: - [ ] **3.6** Implement `ListAgentRuntimes` method with labelSelector support\n48: - [ ] **3.7** Implement `UpdateAgentRuntime` method\n49: - [ ] **3.8** Implement `DeleteAgentRuntime` method\n50: - [ ] **3.9** Implement `GetAgentRuntimeStatus` method\n51: - [ ] **3.10** Implement `PatchAgentRuntimeStatus` method\n52: - [ ] **3.11** Implement `WatchAgentRuntimes` method (for watch=true queries)\n53: - [ ] **3.12** Implement `CreateCodeInterpreter` method\n54: - [ ] **3.13** Implement `GetCodeInterpreter` method\n55: - [ ] **3.14** Implement `ListCodeInterpreters` method with labelSelector support\n56: - [ ] **3.15** Implement `UpdateCodeInterpreter` method\n57: - [ ] **3.16** Implement `DeleteCodeInterpreter` method\n58: - [ ] **3.17** Implement `GetCodeInterpreterStatus` method\n59: - [ ] **3.18** Implement `PatchCodeInterpreterStatus` method\n60: - [ ] **3.19** Implement `WatchCodeInterpreters` method\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: ## Phase 4: Kubernetes Client Integration\n65: \n66: - [ ] **4.1** Implement `NewK8sClient` function in `client.go` - create Kubernetes clientset from kubeconfig\n67: - [ ] **4.2** Implement `NewInClusterClient` function in `client.go` - create client for in-cluster mode\n68: - [ ] **4.3** Implement `NewClientset` function in `client.go` - create typed clientset for AgentCube CRDs\n69: - [ ] **4.4** Implement `NewInformerFactory` function in `client.go` - create SharedInformerFactory\n70: - [ ] **4.5** Implement `RegisterInformers` method in `server.go` - register AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter informers\n71: - [ ] **4.6** Implement `StartInformers` method in `server.go` - start informers and wait for cache sync\n72: - [ ] **4.7** Implement client cleanup in `Close` method - close HTTP clients without goroutine leaks\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ## Phase 5: HTTP Handlers\n77: \n78: - [ ] **5.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/agentruntime.go`\n79: - [ ] **5.2** Implement `HandleCreateAgentRuntime` handler - POST /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes\n80: - [ ] **5.3** Implement `HandleGetAgentRuntime` handler - GET /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes/{name}\n81: - [ ] **5.4** Implement `HandleListAgentRuntimes` handler - GET /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes (with labelSelector, watch)\n82: - [ ] **5.5** Implement `HandleUpdateAgentRuntime` handler - PUT /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes/{name}\n83: - [ ] **5.6** Implement `HandleDeleteAgentRuntime` handler - DELETE /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes/{name}\n84: - [ ] **5.7** Implement `HandleGetAgentRuntimeStatus` handler - GET /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes/{name}/status\n85: - [ ] **5.8** Implement `HandlePatchAgentRuntimeStatus` handler - PATCH /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes/{name}/status\n86: - [ ] **5.9** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/codeinterpreter.go`\n87: - [ ] **5.10** Implement `HandleCreateCodeInterpreter` handler - POST /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/codeinterpreters\n88: - [ ] **5.11** Implement `HandleGetCodeInterpreter` handler - GET /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/codeinterpreters/{name}\n89: - [ ] **5.12** Implement `HandleListCodeInterpreters` handler - GET /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/codeinterpreters\n90: - [ ] **5.13** Implement `HandleUpdateCodeInterpreter` handler - PUT /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/codeinterpreters/{name}\n91: - [ ] **5.14** Implement `HandleDeleteCodeInterpreter` handler - DELETE /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/codeinterpreters/{name}\n92: - [ ] **5.15** Implement `HandleGetCodeInterpreterStatus` handler - GET /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status\n93: - [ ] **5.16** Implement `HandlePatchCodeInterpreterStatus` handler - PATCH /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status\n94: - [ ] **5.17** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go`\n95: - [ ] **5.18** Implement `HandleHealthz` handler - GET /healthz (liveness probe, returns \"ok\")\n96: - [ ] **5.19** Implement `HandleReadyz` handler - GET /readyz (readiness probe, 200 when ready, 503 when not)\n97: - [ ] **5.20** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/metrics.go`\n98: - [ ] **5.21** Implement `HandleMetrics` handler - Prometheus metrics endpoint\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## Phase 6: Middleware Implementation\n103: \n104: - [ ] **6.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging.go`\n105: - [ ] **6.2** Implement `LoggingMiddleware` function - logs method, path, status code, latency\n106: - [ ] **6.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/error.go`\n107: - [ ] **6.4** Define error codes constants in `error.go` (ErrCodeInvalidRequest, ErrCodeNotFound, etc.)\n108: - [ ] **6.5** Implement `ErrorMiddleware` function - map Kubernetes API errors to HTTP status codes\n109: - [ ] **6.6** Implement `handleAPIError` function - structured error response with message, reason, code\n110: - [ ] **6.7** Implement `httpStatusForErrorCode` function - error code to HTTP status mapping\n111: - [ ] **6.8** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors.go`\n112: - [ ] **6.9** Implement `CORSMiddleware` function - handle CORS preflight requests\n113: - [ ] **6.10** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/recovery.go`\n114: - [ ] **6.11** Implement `RecoveryMiddleware` function - recover from panics, return 500\n115: \n116: ---\n117: \n118: ## Phase 7: Server Setup & Graceful Shutdown\n119: \n120: - [ ] **7.1** Implement `NewServer` constructor function in `server.go`\n121: - [ ] **7.2** Implement `setupRouter` method in `server.go` - configure Gin router\n122: - [ ] **7.3** Configure middleware stack (Logging, Recovery, CORS, Error)\n123: - [ ] **7.4** Implement `RegisterRoutes` method - wire up all route groups\n124: - [ ] **7.5** Implement `Start` method - start HTTP server with configurable port\n125: - [ ] **7.6** Implement graceful shutdown logic - stop accepting new requests, finish existing ones\n126: - [ ] **7.7** Handle SIGTERM/SIGINT signals for shutdown trigger\n127: - [ ] **7.8** Implement shutdown timeout handling (default 30 seconds)\n128: - [ ] **7.9** Shutdown informers on server stop\n129: \n130: ---\n131: \n132: ## Phase 8: Configuration & CLI Entry Point\n133: \n134: - [ ] **8.1** Create `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`\n135: - [ ] **8.2** Implement command-line flag parsing (--port, --kubeconfig, etc.)\n136: - [ ] **8.3** Default port: 8080\n137: - [ ] **8.4** Implement environment variable loading\n138: - [ ] **8.5** Wire up configuration from flags/env to `Config` struct\n139: - [ ] **8.6** Initialize Kubernetes client (from kubeconfig or in-cluster)\n140: - [ ] **8.7** Initialize WorkloadManager service\n141: - [ ] **8.8** Initialize and start server\n142: - [ ] **8.9** Handle startup errors and exit gracefully\n143: \n144: ---\n145: \n146: ## Phase 9: Unit Tests\n147: \n148: - [ ] **9.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/mocks_test.go` - mock implementations for testing\n149: - [ ] **9.2** Implement `MockWorkloadManager` struct with function fields\n150: - [ ] **9.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/agentruntime_test.go`\n151: - [ ] **9.4** Test `HandleCreateAgentRuntime` success path (201 Created)\n152: - [ ] **9.5** Test `HandleCreateAgentRuntime` validation failure (400 Bad Request)\n153: - [ ] **9.6** Test `HandleGetAgentRuntime` success path (200 OK)\n154: - [ ] **9.7** Test `HandleGetAgentRuntime` not found (404 Not Found)\n155: - [ ] **9.8** Test `HandleListAgentRuntimes` with pagination\n156: - [ ] **9.9** Test `HandleListAgentRuntimes` with labelSelector\n157: - [ ] **9.10** Test `HandleUpdateAgentRuntime` success path\n158: - [ ] **9.11** Test `HandleDeleteAgentRuntime` success path\n159: - [ ] **9.12** Test `HandleUpdateAgentRuntimeStatus` success path\n160: - [ ] **9.13** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/codeinterpreter_test.go`\n161: - [ ] **9.14** Test all CodeInterpreter handlers (similar to AgentRuntime)\n162: - [ ] **9.15** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health_test.go`\n163: - [ ] **9.16** Test `HandleHealthz` returns 200 OK with \"ok\"\n164: - [ ] **9.17** Test `HandleReadyz` returns 200 OK when ready\n165: - [ ] **9.18** Test `HandleReadyz` returns 503 when not ready\n166: - [ ] **9.19** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging_test.go`\n167: - [ ] **9.20** Test `LoggingMiddleware` logs request details\n168: - [ ] **9.21** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/error_test.go`\n169: - [ ] **9.22** Test `ErrorMiddleware` converts errors to APIResponse\n170: - [ ] **9.23** Test error responses follow Kubernetes Status format\n171: \n172: ---\n173: \n174: ## Phase 10: Integration Tests\n175: \n176: - [ ] **10.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n177: - [ ] **10.2** Test AgentRuntime CRUD end-to-end flow\n178: - [ ] **10.3** Test CodeInterpreter CRUD end-to-end flow\n179: - [ ] **10.4** Test watch functionality streams NDJSON\n180: - [ ] **10.5** Test graceful shutdown under load\n181: \n182: ---\n183: \n184: ## Phase 11: Verification & Coverage\n185: \n186: - [ ] **11.1** Run `go build ./cmd/workload-manager/...` - binary compiles successfully\n187: - [ ] **11.2** Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` - all unit tests pass\n188: - [ ] **11.3** Run `go test -race ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` - no race conditions\n189: - [ ] **11.4** Verify test coverage ≥80% for all packages\n190: - [ ] **11.5** Verify all handlers return correct HTTP status codes\n191: - [ ] **11.6** Verify error responses follow API contract (Kubernetes Status format)\n192: - [ ] **11.7** Verify middleware stack is correctly ordered\n193: - [ ] **11.8** Verify graceful shutdown completes within 30 seconds\n194: - [ ] **11.9** Verify /healthz returns 200 OK with \"ok\"\n195: - [ ] **11.10** Verify /readyz returns 200 when ready, 503 when not\n196: - [ ] **11.11** Run `go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` - no issues\n197: \n198: ---\n199: \n200: ## Verification Checklist (AR-004 Delta Spec Compliance)\n201: \n202: ### HTTP Server Foundation (AR-004-001 to 003)\n203: - [ ] Server initializes with configurable listen address via --port flag (default 8080)\n204: - [ ] Graceful shutdown within 30 seconds\n205: - [ ] /healthz returns 200 OK with \"ok\" and Content-Type text/plain\n206: - [ ] /readyz returns 200 when ready, 503 when not\n207: \n208: ### Kubernetes Client Integration (AR-004-010 to 012)\n209: - [ ] Client can be initialized from kubeconfig\n210: - [ ] Client can be initialized in-cluster\n211: - [ ] HTTP clients are properly closed on shutdown\n212: \n213: ### AgentRuntime CRUD API (AR-004-020 to 027)\n214: - [ ] POST /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes returns 201 Created\n215: - [ ] GET /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes/{name} returns 200 OK\n216: - [ ] GET /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes returns 200 OK with list\n217: - [ ] PUT /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes/{name} returns 200 OK\n218: - [ ] DELETE /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes/{name} returns 200 OK\n219: - [ ] GET .../agentruntimes/{name}/status returns status subresource\n220: - [ ] PATCH .../agentruntimes/{name}/status patches only status\n221: - [ ] GET ...?watch=true streams NDJSON\n222: \n223: ### CodeInterpreter CRUD API (AR-004-030 to 037)\n224: - [ ] Same patterns as AgentRuntime CRUD\n225: \n226: ### Middleware & Observability (AR-004-040 to 042)\n227: - [ ] Request logging middleware logs method, path, status, latency\n228: - [ ] Metrics collection tracks request count, duration histogram\n229: - [ ] Error handling maps K8s errors to HTTP status codes\n230: \n231: ### API Format & Compatibility (AR-004-050 to 051)\n232: - [ ] Content-Type: application/json for requests/responses\n233: - [ ] Error responses follow Kubernetes Status format\n234: \n235: ### Integration with client-go (AR-004-060 to 062)\n236: - [ ] Uses RuntimeV1alpha1 Clientset accessor\n237: - [ ] Uses Informers for list operations (when cache ready)\n238: - [ ] Uses Listers for cached reads\n239: \n240: ---\n241: \n242: ## Dependencies\n243: \n244: | Task | Depends On |\n245: |------|------------|\n246: | Phase 2 | Phase 1 |\n247: | Phase 3 | Phase 2 |\n248: | Phase 4 | Phase 2 |\n249: | Phase 5 | Phase 2, 3, 4 |\n250: | Phase 6 | Phase 2 |\n251: | Phase 7 | Phase 4, 5, 6 |\n252: | Phase 8 | Phase 7 |\n253: | Phase 9 | Phase 5, 6 |\n254: | Phase 10 | Phase 7, 9 |\n255: | Phase 11 | Phase 9, 10 |\n256: \n257: ---\n258: \n259: ## References\n260: \n261: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-004/delta-spec.md`\n262: - client-go: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n263: - AgentRuntime CRD: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n264: - CodeInterpreter CRD: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n265: - API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n\n(End of file - total 265 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 Tasks\n\n**Module:** pkg/workloadmanager  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Directory Scaffold\n\n- [ ] **1.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/` directory structure\n- [ ] **1.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` - API request/re